To solve this problem, you can use a recursive approach with memoization to efficiently calculate the nth Fibonacci number.

```python
def fib(n, memo = {}):
    if n in memo:
        return memo[n]
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    memo[n] = fib(n-1, memo) + fib(n-2, memo)
    return memo[n]
```
